# Task Manager API

A production-ready backend API built using FastAPI, PostgreSQL, and Docker.

---

## Features

- Create, update, delete, and fetch tasks
- Pagination, filtering, and sorting
- Custom error handling (consistent JSON format)
- Logging (request and error logs)
- Database migrations using Alembic
- Environment-based configuration
- Dockerized setup (application + database)
- Automated testing using pytest

---

## Tech Stack

- FastAPI
- PostgreSQL
- SQLAlchemy
- Alembic
- Docker & Docker Compose
- Pytest

---

## Setup & Run

### 1. Clone repository

git clone <your-repo-url>
cd task_manager

---

### 2. Run with Docker

docker-compose up --build

---

### 3. Access API documentation

http://localhost:8000/docs

---

## Run Tests

python -m pytest -q

---

## Project Structure

task_manager/
│── app/
│── tests/
│── alembic/
│── main.py
│── docker-compose.yml
│── requirements.txt

---

## Key Highlights

- One-command startup using Docker
- Production-style error handling
- Clean architecture and modular code
- Fully tested APIs

